<title>CANADA: Four Seasons sells stake in Nevis hotel.</title>
<headline>Four Seasons sells stake in Nevis hotel.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1996-11-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Four Seasons Hotels Inc said it sold its 15 percent interest in the Four Seasons Resort in Nevis as part of a sale of the hotel by the majority owner to a Maritz Wolff limited partnership.</p>
<p>Four Seasons said it would retain management of the hotel under a long-term management agreement enhanced by increased management fees and an extended term.</p>
<p>The Maritz Wolff, a luxury hotel investment fund, owns the Four Seasons hotels in Austin, Texas, Santa Barbara, California and Toronto.</p>
<p>-- Reuters Toronto Bureau  (416) 941-8100</p>
